# image-pipeline — what's ignored and why
#
# This file controls what Git tracks under skills/image-pipeline/. The rule
# is simple: SOURCE is tracked, GENERATED ARTIFACTS are not. If you've added
# a new kind of output that you think should be in version control, prefer
# putting a regenerable copy under assets/ (ignored) and a curated/canonical
# reference under a separate tracked path — don't loosen this file.
#
# Tracked (canonical):
#   - SKILL.md, *.md docs
#   - tools/*.py        (asset_gen.py, comfyui_client.py, zit_styles.py,
#                       style_smoketest.py, pixel_art_toolkit.py, ...)
#   - presets/*.py      (palette / preset registries)
#   - workflows/*.json  (ComfyUI workflow templates)
#
# Ignored (regenerable):
#   - assets/style_smoketest/        — driver output, regen via tools/style_smoketest.py
#   - assets/style_smoketest_*/      — alt-prompt / strength-bumped reruns of the same driver
#   - assets/*_run.log               — log files emitted by smoketest runs
#   - assets/budget.json             — Gemini-fallback runtime budget state
#   - any other transient output under assets/
#
# Re-running tools/style_smoketest.py recreates the entire assets/style_smoketest/
# tree in ~11 minutes (20 styles × ~33s on an RTX 3090). The contact sheet at
# assets/style_smoketest/_contact_sheet.png is the visual reference for the
# style registry — regenerate after any zit_styles.py edit.

# ---- ignored paths ----
assets/
*.log
tools/__pycache__/
presets/__pycache__/
